{
  "video_id": "LV6T2tT6-R4",
  "title": "How to Pair Wine and Cheese, According to One of America's Top Sommeliers",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 101.0,
      "end_time": 2000.0,
      "text": "I'm Patrick Cappiello from Rebelle restaurant"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2000.0,
      "end_time": 2833.0,
      "text": "in New York City,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 2833.0,
      "end_time": 3666.0,
      "text": "and today I'm going to teach you"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 3666.0,
      "end_time": 5909.0,
      "text": "how to pair wine and cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 5909.0,
      "end_time": 8581.0,
      "text": "(upbeat music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 8581.0,
      "end_time": 10301.0,
      "text": "Everyone knows wine and cheese goes together"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 10301.0,
      "end_time": 12520.0,
      "text": "but there are a few rules that I think you can follow"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 12520.0,
      "end_time": 14988.0,
      "text": "that will make your wine and cheese experience even better."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 14988.0,
      "end_time": 17690.0,
      "text": "Most cheese boards, you're going to have a goat cheese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 17690.0,
      "end_time": 20691.0,
      "text": "a cheddar cheese, a washed rind cheese, a blue cheese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 20691.0,
      "end_time": 21918.0,
      "text": "and a firm cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 21918.0,
      "end_time": 25290.0,
      "text": "This is kind of the 101 of cheeseboard creation"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 25290.0,
      "end_time": 27109.0,
      "text": "and with each of these cheeses"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 27109.0,
      "end_time": 28958.0,
      "text": "I think there's a wine that's a good companion."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 28958.0,
      "end_time": 30381.0,
      "text": "Just like food pairing as a whole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 30381.0,
      "end_time": 31712.0,
      "text": "or just say other food pairings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 31712.0,
      "end_time": 33760.0,
      "text": "there's really no one wine that goes with everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 33760.0,
      "end_time": 35797.0,
      "text": "So, you really need to look at each cheese individually"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 35797.0,
      "end_time": 38580.0,
      "text": "to see the best wine to put next to that particular cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 38581.0,
      "end_time": 39891.0,
      "text": "The first cheese we're going to talk about"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 39891.0,
      "end_time": 41650.0,
      "text": "is a goat's milk chevre cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 41651.0,
      "end_time": 42592.0,
      "text": "and with this cheese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 42592.0,
      "end_time": 44771.0,
      "text": "I think sauvignon blanc is really the best pairing."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 44771.0,
      "end_time": 47869.0,
      "text": "Sauvignon blanc that you find in areas like Loire Valley,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 47869.0,
      "end_time": 49510.0,
      "text": "where much goat cheese is made"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 49510.0,
      "end_time": 50558.0,
      "text": "or even stuff in California."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 50558.0,
      "end_time": 52327.0,
      "text": "In the end it's that style of wine"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 52327.0,
      "end_time": 53698.0,
      "text": "that's made from sauvignon blanc"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 53698.0,
      "end_time": 56700.0,
      "text": "that really makes it a good companion for chevre cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 56700.0,
      "end_time": 57458.0,
      "text": "It's about the acidity for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 57458.0,
      "end_time": 59378.0,
      "text": "Really having that acid to help cut through"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 59378.0,
      "end_time": 61436.0,
      "text": "the fattiness and the creaminess of the goat cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 61436.0,
      "end_time": 62916.0,
      "text": "as well as the complimentary flavors."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 62916.0,
      "end_time": 65196.0,
      "text": "There's a grassy aromatic and flavor"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 65196.0,
      "end_time": 66207.0,
      "text": "that you get with sauvignon blanc"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 66207.0,
      "end_time": 67747.0,
      "text": "that I also find in goat cheese as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 67748.0,
      "end_time": 69656.0,
      "text": "Sauvignon blanc and goat's milk chevre."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 69656.0,
      "end_time": 70938.0,
      "text": "Really classic pairing."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 70938.0,
      "end_time": 72227.0,
      "text": "Really delicious pairing."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 72227.0,
      "end_time": 73316.0,
      "text": "The next cheese that we're going to look at"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 73316.0,
      "end_time": 74556.0,
      "text": "is a cheddar cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 74556.0,
      "end_time": 76236.0,
      "text": "This is a Vermont cheddar cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 76236.0,
      "end_time": 78548.0,
      "text": "For me, I really like cheddar cheese and beer"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 78548.0,
      "end_time": 81327.0,
      "text": "and I think that there's a really interesting companionship"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 81327.0,
      "end_time": 83348.0,
      "text": "that happens when you do beer and cheddar cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 83348.0,
      "end_time": 85236.0,
      "text": "and it's a pretty common thing to do as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 85236.0,
      "end_time": 87805.0,
      "text": "But if you want to look at wine to work with cheddar cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 87805.0,
      "end_time": 88927.0,
      "text": "I like sparkling wine."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 88927.0,
      "end_time": 90807.0,
      "text": "For me, something like champagne is perfect."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 90807.0,
      "end_time": 92476.0,
      "text": "You can also do pét-nats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 92476.0,
      "end_time": 94416.0,
      "text": "which are naturally made sparkling wines."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 94416.0,
      "end_time": 96926.0,
      "text": "Even cider works really well with cheddar cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 96927.0,
      "end_time": 98906.0,
      "text": "So, again, the idea of cheddar cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 98906.0,
      "end_time": 101407.0,
      "text": "The fact that is has a rich, creamy texture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 101407.0,
      "end_time": 102386.0,
      "text": "but it's pretty powerful"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 102386.0,
      "end_time": 104946.0,
      "text": "and I think the fattiness can benefit from bubbles."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 104946.0,
      "end_time": 108140.0,
      "text": "Bubbles and cheddar, for me, that's really a great pairing"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 108140.0,
      "end_time": 109178.0,
      "text": "and a pairing that helps to compliment"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 109178.0,
      "end_time": 110250.0,
      "text": "both the cheese and the wine."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 110250.0,
      "end_time": 112439.0,
      "text": "So the next cheese we're going to look at is a firm cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 112439.0,
      "end_time": 114348.0,
      "text": "This particular cheese is Comté,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 114348.0,
      "end_time": 116929.0,
      "text": "which is a cheese that comes from the Jura in France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 116930.0,
      "end_time": 118209.0,
      "text": "right on the border of Switzerland."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 118209.0,
      "end_time": 119388.0,
      "text": "Like most firm cheeses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 119388.0,
      "end_time": 121319.0,
      "text": "it can have a really nutty flavor profile"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 121319.0,
      "end_time": 122907.0,
      "text": "so I like really nutty wines with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 122907.0,
      "end_time": 124777.0,
      "text": "This is an example of a wine that comes from the Jura"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 124778.0,
      "end_time": 126957.0,
      "text": "the same place that this Comté is from"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 126957.0,
      "end_time": 129790.0,
      "text": "and it's a more oxidized style of white wine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 129789.99999999999,
      "end_time": 132428.0,
      "text": "similar to like a Sherry or a skin fermented white wine."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 132428.0,
      "end_time": 134347.0,
      "text": "It has a nutty, rich texture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 134348.0,
      "end_time": 137418.0,
      "text": "white wines that have more of a red wine weight to them"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 137418.0,
      "end_time": 139980.0,
      "text": "which is really what you need ideally"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 139980.0,
      "end_time": 140799.0,
      "text": "for a pairing with firm cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 140799.0,
      "end_time": 142680.0,
      "text": "Also, wines from Sherry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 142680.0,
      "end_time": 144456.0,
      "text": "like a dry Sherry from Jerez in Spain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 144456.0,
      "end_time": 145809.0,
      "text": "also a great companion."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 145809.0,
      "end_time": 147418.0,
      "text": "And I think additionally, skin fermented white wines"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 147418.0,
      "end_time": 148799.0,
      "text": "that you can find in northern Italy"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 148799.0,
      "end_time": 151108.0,
      "text": "would also be great pairings for firm cheeses."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 151108.0,
      "end_time": 153298.0,
      "text": "So, for our soft, washed rind cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 153298.0,
      "end_time": 155119.0,
      "text": "we have a wine from the Burgundy region in France"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 155119.0,
      "end_time": 156518.0,
      "text": "called Époisses."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 156518.0,
      "end_time": 157599.0,
      "text": "For soft cheeses, I think you can either use"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 157599.0,
      "end_time": 159329.0,
      "text": "fuller bodied white wines"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 159330.0,
      "end_time": 161498.0,
      "text": "or I like a lighter bodied red wine."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 161498.0,
      "end_time": 164209.0,
      "text": "So, Pinot Noir is a really awesome pairing with this."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 164210.0,
      "end_time": 165938.0,
      "text": "It's grown in the Burgundy region of France"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 165938.0,
      "end_time": 167338.0,
      "text": "so again you see an example of a wine"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 167338.0,
      "end_time": 169537.0,
      "text": "that is from the same area as the cheese comes from"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 169538.0,
      "end_time": 170508.0,
      "text": "but with soft cheeses"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 170508.0,
      "end_time": 172148.0,
      "text": "because the flavors are very subtle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 172148.0,
      "end_time": 174388.0,
      "text": "I think you need a subtle wine like Pinot Noir."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 174388.0,
      "end_time": 175610.0,
      "text": "It's not going to be too overpowering"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 175610.0,
      "end_time": 177828.0,
      "text": "and help enhance the flavors of that cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 177828.0,
      "end_time": 179839.0,
      "text": "The last cheese that we have is a blue cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 179839.0,
      "end_time": 182919.0,
      "text": "and for me, the classing pairing for blue cheese is port."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 182919.0,
      "end_time": 184548.0,
      "text": "This is a great example of a tawny port."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 184548.0,
      "end_time": 187738.0,
      "text": "So, ports are rich, full bodied red wines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 187738.0,
      "end_time": 190900.0,
      "text": "but wines that often have a bit of sweetness."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 190900.0,
      "end_time": 192649.0,
      "text": "Because blue cheese be a little funky, kind of salty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 192650.0,
      "end_time": 194890.0,
      "text": "that sweetness and that full body really helps"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 194890.0,
      "end_time": 196689.0,
      "text": "to offset those flavors, enhance them"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 196689.0,
      "end_time": 197959.0,
      "text": "and really make an awesome pairing."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 197959.0,
      "end_time": 200490.0,
      "text": "It's a classic pairing, and classic for a reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 200490.0,
      "end_time": 201570.0,
      "text": "So I think we've seen today that wine and cheese"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 201570.0,
      "end_time": 202858.0,
      "text": "can work really well together."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 202858.0,
      "end_time": 203997.0,
      "text": "And there's a lot of options"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 203997.0,
      "end_time": 205778.0,
      "text": "to make your wine and cheese pairing perfect."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 205778.0,
      "end_time": 207628.0,
      "text": "So in the end, you should open a lot of wine"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 207628.0,
      "end_time": 209780.0,
      "text": "and eat a lot of cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 209800.0,
      "end_time": 212300.0,
      "text": "I'm Patrick Cappiello from Playboy.com"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 212300.0,
      "end_time": 215800.0,
      "text": "This is Mardon, a little grower that's making some of the most spectacular wines in the area."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 216000.0,
      "end_time": 221000.0,
      "text": "A family-run domain that produces really mineral-driven and focus-style sauvignon blanc."
    }
  ]
}